    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-07-01T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-07-01T05:00:00-05:00" n="562"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d562">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">653.003/146: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lisbon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-07-01T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 1, 1934—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 1—10:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4. Decree effective today raises the existing surtax on imports of 20% to 28% and
                    creates a special surtax on exports of 13½% for merchandise transported in
                    vessels of countries which have not secured abolition of flag discrimination
                    unless these countries do so by August 1st. Portuguese vessels and those of
                    countries whose treaties give them national treatment are exempted from the
                    increased rates but will not continue to receive the previous reductions on
                    existing duties. <pb facs="0779" n="679" xml:id="pg_679"/> Great Britain, France
                    and the Netherlands now have such treaties and Germany is completing
                    negotiations. Gasoline, mineral oils, coal and sugar are exempt from the
                    discriminatory rates.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caldwell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
